title: New York Jets Provided With Toilet Paper for London Trip
text:
Get Sports Alerts 
1 Oct 2015 04:47 PM EST 
After learning last November they would be playing a game overseas, the New York Jets sent a liaison to figure out a travel plan for the team. Almost a year ahead of the 2015 season, their senior manager of operations began preparing for their 65 hours across the Pond this week. Arriving in London on Friday, the team will spend the weekend in England for their Sunday morning contest. But what does an NFL team bring along for their international rider? Among the items shipped overseas for the AFC East team, 350 rolls of toilet paper will greet the organization in Europe. Toilet paper sold in England, was too thin according to a report by the New York Times. Their game at Wembley Stadium against the Miami Dolphins is scheduled for Sunday at 9:30 a.m. Eastern Standard.
